10:T15df,1. Use the attached reference images of Luna as the subject. Recreate her exact likeness faithfully — fluffy white cat, real facial injuries, swollen and damaged eyes, matted fur near wounds. Do not clean up or alter her injuries.
Vertical 9:16 iPhone photo. Luna is being held gently against someone's chest — cradled upright, her injured face resting on a shoulder or tucked against a collarbone. The human holding her is wearing a plain everyday t-shirt or hoodie — grey, navy, white, nothing special. The fabric is slightly wrinkled and real. Only the lower part of the person's chin and neck is visible at the top of the frame — not their full face. Just enough human presence to feel real.
Luna's injured face is turned outward toward the camera — her damaged eyes looking directly into the lens over the person's shoulder. The direct eye contact over a human shoulder is the emotional core of this image. She looks simultaneously safe and in danger.
The photo is taken with an iPhone selfie-style from a slight distance — arm extended, slightly above eye level. The background is a blurred home interior. Warm lamp light from behind creating a slight rim light on Luna's white fur. iPhone front camera quality — slightly lower resolution, slightly wider lens distortion, authentic selfie texture.
Natural iPhone processing — warm automatic white balance, slight lens flare from the background lamp, moderate digital noise. Looks exactly like a selfie someone took holding their injured cat because they needed people to see how bad it has gotten.
Text in plain white iPhone font, placed naturally:
Top in small text:
"holding her and just hoping"
Bottom in bold direct text:
"Click the link. Any amount helps. Luna needs surgery to survive."

2. Use the attached reference images of Luna as the subject. Recreate her exact likeness faithfully. Small fluffy white cat, visible facial injuries, swollen damaged eyes, real wounds intact. Do not alter her appearance.
Vertical 9:16 phone photo taken inside a car. Luna is in someone's lap or in an open carrier on the passenger seat. The windshield and blurred road ahead are faintly visible in the background — out of focus but recognizable. Daylight streaming through the car windows creates slightly harsh uneven lighting across Luna's face and fur.
Luna is looking up toward the camera — tired, still, trusting. Her injured face is the center of the entire image. The car interior around her is ordinary — a seat belt visible, a dashboard blurred, real life context. Someone is driving her somewhere and someone else is in the passenger seat photographing her because they don't know what else to do.
Authentic phone photo quality — slight motion blur from the moving car, digital grain, windshield glare slightly present. Colors are natural and unedited. This should look exactly like a photo someone took on the way to an emergency vet appointment.
Text placed casually in plain white font as if added quickly in Instagram stories:
Top:
"on the way to the vet again 😔"
Bottom in bold urgent text:
"We can't afford the surgery without your help. Donate any amount — link in bio. Please share this."
Feels completely native. Zero design polish. All emotion.

3. Use the attached reference images of Luna as the subject. Recreate her exact likeness faithfully — small fluffy white cat, real visible facial injuries, swollen and damaged eyes, soft white fur matted near wounds. Do not heal or soften her injuries in any way.
Vertical 9:16 phone photo. Luna is lying on a pillow on a bed — someone's actual pillow, slightly dented, ordinary pillowcase, nothing staged. She is resting her injured face on the pillow looking directly into the camera. The photo is taken from pillow level — the camera is on the mattress shooting straight at her face. Intimate. Close. Like someone lying next to their sick cat unable to sleep.
Lighting is the soft warm glow of a bedside lamp only. Everything else is dark. Her white fur catches the warm light on one side, the other side falls into soft shadow. The background is a dark bedroom — barely visible. Heavy digital grain from the low light phone camera. Slightly soft focus. Authentic and deeply personal.
Text overlays in plain casual white Instagram stories font — placed imperfectly as if typed in a hurry:
Top of screen:
"I can't sleep knowing she might not make it"
Bottom of screen in slightly larger bold text:
"LINK IN BIO — every $10 gets her closer to surgery. please donate tonight."
Raw, undesigned, zero polish. Looks like a real person's story post at midnight.

4. Using the attached reference images of Luna, recreate her exact likeness. Small fluffy white cat, real facial injuries, swollen damaged eyes, matted white fur. Every wound faithful to reference photos.
Vertical 9:16 iPhone quality. Luna is on the other side of a glass door or sliding glass door — the camera is outside shooting through the glass at her. She is sitting just inside pressed against the glass her injured face looking out toward the camera. The glass creates a very slight distortion and reflection — the outside world faintly reflected in the glass over her image. Condensation or smudges on the glass slightly obscuring parts of her. She is right there on the other side and the glass between the camera and her feels like the most devastating metaphor — so close but separated. Natural outdoor light hitting the glass from outside. Her white fur and injured face pressing against the cold glass from inside.
